    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the PP attaches to the VP as an adjunct, it typically branches off as a sister to the direct object NP, or sometimes directly under the VP, marked as an adjunct modifier. For a complement attachment, the PP would usually be structurally incorporated *into* the NP, perhaps as a modifier within that NP's structure. The key difference is whether the PP modifies the main action (VP) or one of the constituents within the object (NP).",
