      "content": "While there isn't one single \"messy\" standard, the difference is in the *scope* of the division. When the PP modifies the VP, the division is relatively straightforward: VP splits into V, NP (object), and the adjunct PP. In contrast, if the PP modifies the NP, the NP node itself becomes more complex, potentially splitting into the head N, a modifier NP, and the PP as part of that NP's structure. The complexity comes from the internal constituency of the NP versus the external modification of the VP.",
